quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,89,"O my people! Let not my dispute with you bring upon you the doom similar to that of the people of Noah or of Hud or of Saleh, nor are the people of Lot far off from you"
  11,90,"seek forgiveness of your Lord and turn to Him in repentance; for my Lord is indeed Merciful, Affectionate"
  11,91,"They said: \"O Shu'aib! We do not comprehend much of what you say. In fact, we see that you are a powerless person among us. Were it not for your family, we certainly would have stoned you, for you are not strong enough to prevail against us"
  11,92,"He said: \"O my people! Do you regard my family to be more powerful than Allah, that you have disregarded Him totally as a thing cast behind your back? Surely my Lord encompasses all that you do"
  11,93,"O my people! You keep on doing your way, and I shall keep up mine: soon you will find out who receives the disgraceful punishment and who is a liar! Wait if you will; I too am waiting with you"
  11,94,"When Our judgement came to pass, We delivered Shu'aib and those who believed with him through Our special mercy. A mighty blast seized the wrongdoers and they lay dead with their faces down in their homes by the morning"
  11,95,"as if they had never flourished there. Behold! Like Thamud, gone are the people of Median"
  11,96,We sent Moses with Our signs and clear authority
  11,97,"to Pharoah (Pharaoh) and his chiefs; but they followed the command of Pharoah, and the command of Pharoah was not right"